        <div n="915-303B" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-915-303B-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-915-303B-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-915-303B-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-915-303B-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-915-303B-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-915-303B-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-915-303B-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-915-303B-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-915-303B-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-1"> In youth exalted high in Air,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-2"> Or basking in y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Waters clear,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-3"> Nature to form me took delight</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-4"> And clad my Body all in white</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-5"> My Person tall──my slender waist</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-6"> On either side, w<hi rend="sup">tḥ</hi> fringes grac'd</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-7"> Till me y<hi rend="sup">t</hi> Tyrant Man espy'd</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-8"> And drag'd me from my Mother's side</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-9"> No wonder now I look so thin</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-10"> The Tyrant strip'd me to my Skin</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-11"> My skin he strip'd──my hair he crop'd</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-12"> At Head──and Foot──my Body lop'd</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-13"> And then w<hi rend="sup">th</hi></l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="14" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-14"> heart more hard than Stone&#13;</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-15"> He pick'd y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Marrow from y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> bone</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-16"> To vex me more──he took A freak</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-17"> To slit my Tongue──and make me speak</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-18"> But that w<hi rend="sup">cḥ</hi> wonderfull appear's</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-19"> I speak to eyes──and not to Ears<gap/><gap/></l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-20"> To me he chiefly gives in trust</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-21"> To please his malice──or his lust.</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-22"> From me no Secret he can hide</l><l n="23" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-23"> I see his Malice──and his Pride.</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-24"> And my delight──is to expose</l><l n="25" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-25"> His follys──to his greatest foes──</l><l n="26" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-26"> All languages──I can command</l><l n="27" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-27"> And yet no word I understand</l><l n="28" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-28"> W<hi rend="sup">tḥ</hi>out my Aid──y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> best divine</l><l n="29" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-29"> In Learning, woud not know A line</l><l n="30" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-30"> The Lawyer must forget his pleading</l><l n="31" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-31"> The Schollor woud not shew his reading</l><l n="32" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-32"> Nay Man──my Master──is my Slave</l><l n="33" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-33"> I give command──to kill──or Save</l><l n="34" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-34"> And grant ten thousand Pound A year</l><l n="35" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-35"> And make A Beggar, strut A Peer</l><l n="36" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-36"> But while I thus──my life relate,</l><l n="37" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-37"> I only hasten on my fate──</l><l n="38" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-38"> My tongue is black──my Mouth is furr'd</l><l n="39" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-39"> I hardly now, can force A word</l><l n="40" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-40"> I die unpitty'd──and forgot</l><l n="41" xml:id="spp-915-303B-line-41"> And on some Dunghill left to rott915-303B   </l></lg></div>
